To get the maximum route number per process based on license, you can use the following command in the OSPF module:

show ip ospf route | sort route-number | show license

This command will show the list of all the routes that are known to the router, along with their route numbers. The route numbers are sorted in ascending order, so the maximum route number will be at the top of the list. The "show license" command will display the license information for the router, which will include the license value.

For example, the output of this command might look like this:

Router# show ip ospf route | sort route-number | show license

Maximum route number: 100 (license value: 10000)
